---
description: Build backend and frontend changes from explicit API contracts
globs: **/*.{ts,tsx}
alwaysApply: false
---

# API Contract First

- Define request and response schemas before wiring endpoint or screen logic.
- Validate all external input at the boundary (body, params, query, headers).
- Keep API payloads stable; avoid ad-hoc response shape changes.
- Share or mirror domain types across frontend and backend to avoid drift.
- Add graceful handling for contract errors (400/401/403/404/500) on both sides.
- When changing a contract, update caller code and docs in the same task.
